🧱 1. Abstraction in JavaScript
- Abstraction means exposing only essential features and hiding the internal details.
- JavaScript supports this using classes, where methods can abstract away complex logic.

🐙 2. Polymorphism in JavaScript
- Polymorphism lets multiple classes define different versions of the same method.
- Achieved via method overriding in JavaScript.

🔐 3. Encapsulation in JavaScript
- Encapsulation means protecting data by restricting direct access.
- You can use JavaScript's private fields using #

🧬 4. Inheritance in JavaScript
- Inheritance lets one class extend another and inherit its properties/methods.
- Done using the extends keyword.